Employee-Department System

A simple Spring Boot REST API to manage employees and departments with many-to-many relationships.  

### Features: 
- Add Employees & Departments  
- Enroll Employees in Departments  
- Fetch Employees & Their Departments  
- Update & Delete Records  

### **Tech Stack:**  
- Backend: Spring Boot, JPA, Hibernate  
- Database: MySQL  

### **Endpoints:**  
- `POST /emp` â€“ Add Employee  
- `POST /dept` â€“ Add Department  
- `POST /enroll/{empId}/{deptId}` â€“ Enroll Employee in Department  
- `GET /getemp/{id}` â€“ Get Employee by ID  
- `GET /emp/{id}/dept` â€“ Get Employee's Departments  
- `PUT /emp/{id}` â€“ Update Employee (to be implemented)  
- `DELETE /emp/{id}` â€“ Delete Employee (to be implemented)  

### **Setup & Run:**  
1. Clone the repo:  
   ```
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/Employee-Department-API.git
   ```  
2. Configure MySQL in `application.properties`  
3. Run the application:  
   ```
   mvn spring-boot:run
   ```  

